 vicinity of the truncation radius along\nopened-up stellar magnetic field lines, remain the same, and are distinct from\nthose of the mechanism proposed by Shu et al. We show that the simulated\noutflow can in principle account for the main observed characteristics of FUOR\nwinds, including the photospheric line shifts measured in FU Ori.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 12 Jun 2011 23:03:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-28"}
